reviews.snippet:
I've been interning in Shibuya for the past two months, and this has quickly become one of my absolute favorite places to eat. The food is consistently amazing and the prices are incredibly reasonable, especially considering the generous portion sizes.

While customer service is already excellent throughout Japan, the staff here truly go above and beyond. Everyone is so friendly and welcoming. Tonight, I had the chance to chat with the owner, and you can really tell how genuine and authentic he is. It made the experience even more special.

If you can, I highly recommend sitting inside. Whether you're living in Tokyo or just visiting, this place is absolutely worth a stop. You won’t regret it!

reviews.snippet:
初めてケバブを食べました。
夜８時にスペシャル ケバブ ラップのチキン(700円)を１つ購入。
辛さはミディアム。
本当はビーフを食べたかったもののチキンに。
店員さんは日本語が苦手なようですが、料理番号とチキンとかミディアムとか言って注文完了。
会計はPayPayも使用できますが現金で行きました。
イートインもできるようですが、持ち帰って自宅で食べました。

半分に切ってガブリ、ソースがジュワッとえもいわれぬ旨さです。チキンも美味しい。オーロラソースのような色合いで複雑な味でほんのり辛い。これは旨いですね。
薄焼きパン（ユフカ？ラバッシュ？）が不思議な食感。

１つでかなりのボリューム。ビール１本で食べておなかいっぱいな感じでした。このご時世に７００円とはリーズナブルｗ
なぜ今まで食べなかったんだろう？と後悔．．．

次回はビーフの出来たてを食べます。
ごちそうさまでした。

extracted_snippet.translated:
I ate kebab for the first time.

I bought one special kebab wrap chicken (700 yen) at 8pm.

I chose medium spiciness.

I actually wanted beef, but I went for chicken.

The waiter didn't seem to be good at Japanese, but I completed my order by saying the dish number and chicken or medium.

I could pay with PayPay, but I paid with cash.

You can eat in, but I took it home and ate it.

I cut it in half and took a bite. The sauce was juicy and indescribably delicious. The chicken was also delicious. It had a complex flavor and a slight spiciness, similar to aurora sauce. It was delicious.

The thin bread (yufka? lavash?) had a strange texture.

One was quite filling. I ate it with one beer and felt full. 700 yen is reasonable in this day and age lol.

I regret why I hadn't tried it before.

Next time I'll try the freshly cooked beef.
Thank you for the meal.
